I converted the `icon.ico` to `icon.bmp` in Sample-Dash-Game, but was then told I needed `SDL2_image.dll` in order to load it. Fine, I [downloaded](http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_image/) the Windows x64 dll and put it in the `Binaries` folder. But now I'm running into this issue which doesn't make sense:

![image-load](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/512416/5077644/66391b5a-6e73-11e4-96ed-d90fd3b4083f.PNG)

@Berulacks Could you look into what is necessary to get icons working on Windows and Linux? Don't kill yourself on this if you have other stuff you can code, but it's one of those minor polish items that makes Dash feel more complete.
